    %p The teens 11–19 are generally formed by combining the unit with the suffix <i>-déc</i>, related to <i>dec</i> “ten”. This same construction was used in classical Latin, but only the numbers 11 through 15 are direct descendents from the Latin originals; 16 through 19 are later creations based on the same pattern.
